      "body" : "@UlysseMizrahi it all depends on what you match on, but yes if you&#39;re writing library code, it can be dangerous to only rely on name. I usually check for a specific annotation, or a particular method signature, like &quot;static method that takes a String and returns an instance of the class&quot;, then assert that there is only one such method found."
