    "answer_id" : 61008345,
    "question_id" : 2467544,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>public class Add {\n    static int add(int a, int b){\n        return (a+b);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>In the above example, 'add' is a static method that takes two integers as arguments.</p>\n<p>Following snippet is used to call 'add' method with input 1 and 2.</p>\n<pre><code>Class myClass = Class.forName(&quot;Add&quot;);\nMethod method = myClass.getDeclaredMethod(&quot;add&quot;, int.class, int.class);\nObject result = method.invoke(null, 1, 2);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2520941,
      "reputation" : 958,
      "user_id" : 2360439,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ea15adeb0df45f8e17bbb06e507a8cf3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "D.A.H",
